														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4735036">
									

<p>I'm going to radically disagree with this take. Interpersonal relationship issues get thrust into professional settings <em>all the time</em>. In an organization like the Foundation, I'm sure it happens even more frequently. When security clearances make an already niche sector of the work force even more isolated, it is common for interpersonal relationships to form.</p>
<p>I think this is an excellent take because it 100% felt like an upset and self-absorbed person was using Foundation resources to try and blame anyone else other than himself. Would this result in disciplinary action? Absolutely it would. Does that mean that it wouldn't exist? No.</p>
<p>Frankly, this article makes me realize that there are likely lots and lots of these kinds of things, and Capt. Kirby just put a human face on the thing that often gets forgotten.</p>
<p>The Foundationverse has people in it. Not just monsters and the inhuman humans that fight those monsters.</p>
<p>Kirby, this gets an easy +1 from me. Thank you for writing it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
