					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/captain-kirby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3440103); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3440103&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183477" alt="Captain Kirby" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3440103)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/captain-kirby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3440103); return false;" >Captain Kirby</a></span> <span class="odate time_1596466129 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Aug 2020 14:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4737548">
									

<p>While I do understand that this requires a bit more suspension of disbelief in some places, I think you may have missed 2 things about why (at least in my opinion) this fits the format:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>So, first of all there is something that could be considered anomalous at play. I may have been a little vague about it, but I intended to imply that Rivera did in fact wipe her own memory. So, since Verity is noticing what may appear to be anomalous symptoms, it makes some sense he would frame this in context of a report. Of course, by creating a report like this there’s already some denial at play, but it’s not like he’s actually experiencing normal communication issues. Besides, submitting an HR report for non-anomalous refusal to talk to him would require him to admit to himself that she’s doing this to him on purpose.</p>
<p>As for Frie’s comments, these are her writing down her thoughts while reviewing the piece for Verity (As an aside, my head canon is that she only reviews the piece because Verity asks her to). But none of them make it through at the end. Like, she removes all of her venting at the end because she realizes she shouldn’t be using the document for her passive aggressiveness anyways.</p>
<p>At the end of the day, it’s totally fine if the format ruins it for you. Honestly I feel bad that the framing impacts your enjoyment of the story that much but I feel like to tell the story the way I want to, this is actually the best format to use to both let the reader see through Verity’s twisted view, while also giving Frie a voice to refute him.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

